Subject: Codex LM Studio Orchestrator Runbook

Description: Supervised runbook for using LM Studio as a local manager over Codex-authored SOP streams and Codex CLI as the OpenAI-backed worker lane.

@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\CodexLMStudioOrchestrationWorkspace.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\SOPTaskManager.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\TaskFrameLaunchQueue.sop

& [CodexLMStudioOrchestratorRunbook] is the supervised operating procedure
  + [runbook_status] is scaffold_ready
  + [stage_001_verify_local_provider] is confirm LM Studio endpoint and selected manager model are available
  + [stage_002_compile_context_stream] is Codex writes or selects current focal point, task frame, source slice, attention kernel, queue state, expected output, proof gates, and outside
  + [stage_003_boot_lm_studio_manager] is send SOP language primer, worker boot packet, and codex_context_stream to LM Studio through codex.cmd local-provider or compatible endpoint
  + [stage_004_capture_manager_proposal] is store raw LM Studio manager output as a codex_job_proposal or blocked_outside note
  + [stage_005_codex_launch_review] is Codex checks authority, cost, scope, command, capture target, proof gate, tests, and dirty-file boundaries
  + [stage_006_dispatch_openai_codex_worker] is run Codex CLI with OpenAI inference only after stage_005 passes
  + [stage_007_capture_validate_integrate] is capture worker output, review diff, run validation, integrate or reject, then commit, push, and tick
  + [stage_008_reenter_or_stop] is continue only when next_step is safe, visible, and bounded
  + [manager_command_shape] is codex.cmd --oss --local-provider lmstudio -m openai/gpt-oss-20b -C <scratch_workspace> -a never -s read-only --output-last-message <capture_target> exec <prompt_packet>
  + [worker_command_shape] is codex.cmd -C C:\Project\Pinky -a never -s workspace-write --output-last-message <capture_target> exec <worker_packet>
  + [command_shape_status] is illustrative and must be inspected before each launch
  + [runbook_outside] is direct daemon launch, missing capture, hidden credentials, unbounded token spend, unrelated dirty files, and destructive shell commands

  = must: inspect command shapes before launch
  = must: keep LM Studio manager runs non-mutating
  = must: keep OpenAI Codex worker runs bounded by a worker packet and capture target
  = must: stop on failed provider, failed validation, unclear authority, explicit user stop, or budget/concurrency cap
  = should: use manager dry runs until proposal fidelity is stable across several task types
  - never: run an invisible background loop from this runbook alone

(codex_lmstudio_orchestrator_runbook) :manager_proposal: /codex_launch_review and capture/ |runbook_outside|
  + [manager_proposal] is LM Studio output captured before launch
  + [codex_launch_review] is authority and safety review
  + [capture] is raw output, diff, tests, validation, integration, and loop tick
  |runbook_outside| unbounded daemon, missing capture, credentials, destructive commands, and hidden spend
